article.headline: Fresno State 69, Hawaii 60
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Shantay Legans scored 25 points and Mustafa Al-Sayyad added 24 as Fresno State completed a season sweep of Hawaii with a 69-60 victory over the Rainbows on Saturday night. Fresno State (14-14, 10-8 Western Athletic Conference) recorded back-to-back victories for the first time since Jan. 15 by making 21-of-24 free throws and limiting Hawaii to 38.3 percent shooting from the field. Julian Sensley, a one-time Fresno State recuit, led Hawaii (19-10, 11-7) with 24 points, making 9-of-10 field-goal attempts. Hawaii's Michael Kuebler, averaging 18.4 points per game, was held to just nine points on 3-of-16 shooting. Kuebler made just 1-of-10 3-pointers. Coming off a career-best 30 points Thursday against San Jose State, Legans made 5-of-11 3-pointers and all six of his free throws. Al-Sayyad finished 8-of-10 from the field and also grabbed a game-high 11 rebounds. Hawaii, which trailed 38-26 at halftime, committed just six turnovers compared to 16 for the Bulldogs. Fresno State began WAC play Jan. 3 with a 69-58 victory over Hawaii in Honolulu. The victory gave Fresno State the No. 6 seed in the WAC tournament, which begins Tuesday in Fresno with games involving the lower seeds. The Bulldogs will oppose No. 3 Boise State Thursday, while No. 3 seed Hawaii meets No. 4 Rice. Nevada clinched the tournament's top seed by thrashing San Jose State 74-45.
